{"id": "EUVD-2018-3275", "enisaUuid": "b9c3927a-e2c8-3819-b452-773005520f0f", "description": "In Git before 2.13.7, 2.14.x before 2.14.4, 2.15.x before 2.15.2, 2.16.x before 2.16.4, and 2.17.x before 2.17.1, remote code execution can occur. With a crafted .gitmodules file, a malicious project can execute an arbitrary script on a machine that runs \"git clone --recurse-submodules\" because submodule \"names\" are obtained from this file, and then appended to $GIT_DIR/modules, leading to directory traversal with \"../\" in a name. Finally, post-checkout hooks from a submodule are executed, bypassing the intended design in which hooks are not obtained from a remote server.", "datePublished": "2018-05-30T04:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T08:01:52", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.0", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2018-11235.html", "https://www.debian.org/security/2018/dsa-4212", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2018:2147", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2018:1957", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2018-11235", "https://advisories.mageia.org/CVE-2018-11235.html", "https://security.archlinux.org/CVE-2018-11235", "https://alas.aws.amazon.com/cve/html/CVE-2018-11235.html", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2018-11235.html", "https://packetstormsecurity.com/files/cve/CVE-2018-11235", "https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/44822/", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3671-1/", "https://marc.info/?l=git&m=152761328506724&w=2", "http://www.securitytracker.com/id/1040991", "https://security.gentoo.org/glsa/201805-13", "http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/104345", "https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/devops/2018/05/29/announcing-the-may-2018-git-security-vulnerability/", "http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2020-05/msg00003.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2018-11235"], "assigner": "mitre", "epss": 39.68, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "b6de2f72-07fa-3a17-a283-f2d072dee47a", "pro